14
00:03:11,393 --> 00:03:14,109
Here's your vegetable soup, Sakura.

15
00:03:14,110 --> 00:03:15,810
Thank you.

16
00:03:19,112 --> 00:03:21,001
It's a nice day
to admire the cherry blossoms.

17
00:03:21,002 --> 00:03:22,298
Agreed.

18
00:03:22,299 --> 00:03:24,203
The sunshine is so warm and cosy.

19
00:03:24,802 --> 00:03:26,803
Looks like it's going to
start raining next week.

20
00:03:26,804 --> 00:03:29,397
This could be the last chance
to see the cherry blossoms this year.

21
00:03:29,398 --> 00:03:32,106
I'm glad we came out
while the sun was still out.

22
00:03:33,295 --> 00:03:34,938
We started having cherry blossom drives

23
00:03:34,939 --> 00:03:38,105
after you got your driving license.

24
00:03:38,106 --> 00:03:39,903
This year marks...

25
00:03:40,308 --> 00:03:41,511
The third time.

26
00:03:41,512 --> 00:03:42,888
Yeah!

27
00:03:43,514 --> 00:03:45,298
It'll be great to come see

28
00:03:45,299 --> 00:03:47,408
the cherry blossoms every year.

29
00:03:48,894 --> 00:03:52,023
You're going to college.
Who can say for sure?

30
00:03:53,111 --> 00:03:55,007
You have a point.

31
00:03:55,693 --> 00:03:58,905
What do you plan to do after graduating?

32
00:04:14,903 --> 00:04:16,606
Well...

33
00:04:23,793 --> 00:04:27,390
"NADESHIKO"
Going cherry blossom viewing with Sakura.

34
00:04:27,391 --> 00:04:29,006
Rin is solo-camping.

35
00:04:29,007 --> 00:04:31,898
Nadeshiko and her sister
are viewing cherry blossoms.

36
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:34,892
Let's get going, Chikuwa.

37
00:04:42,502 --> 00:04:44,195
Chikuwa, look over here!

38
00:04:55,893 --> 00:04:57,508
Hyah.

39
00:05:01,612 --> 00:05:03,605
Such a pleasant day.

40
00:05:03,606 --> 00:05:05,804
Today might be perfect for camping.

41
00:05:08,195 --> 00:05:09,299
What's wrong?

42
00:05:12,394 --> 00:05:14,798
Oh my, do you like that bag?

43
00:05:16,607 --> 00:05:19,606
You really do like
squeezing into narrow spaces.

44
00:05:20,398 --> 00:05:22,216
Such a good dog.

45
00:05:23,497 --> 00:05:26,908
Good dog.

46
00:05:27,804 --> 00:05:28,898
Was that too much?

47
00:05:32,596 --> 00:05:34,897
The whole place
is full of cherry blossoms!

48
00:05:34,898 --> 00:05:37,095
Ena, where are you headed today?

49
00:05:37,096 --> 00:05:38,590
The weather seems nice.

50
00:05:38,591 --> 00:05:40,213
I took Chikuwa with me

51
00:05:40,214 --> 00:05:42,507
and went for a walk in Fujikawa Park.

52
00:05:43,196 --> 00:05:45,001
It's slowly getting warmer lately.

53
00:05:45,002 --> 00:05:47,798
This is perfect for Chikuwa
since it never likes cold days.

54
00:05:47,799 --> 00:05:51,084
I thought so too.
I didn't put thick clothes on it,

55
00:05:51,085 --> 00:05:54,194
but it still felt cold somehow.
It's cooped up in the bag.

56
00:05:54,195 --> 00:05:56,586
It looks like a turtle.

57
00:05:57,392 --> 00:05:59,608
Today is the end
of your business trip, right?

58
00:06:00,002 --> 00:06:03,293
I get two days off
after I get off work this afternoon.

59
00:06:03,294 --> 00:06:04,209
Sorry.

60
00:06:04,210 --> 00:06:05,111
It's my bad

61
00:06:05,112 --> 00:06:07,314
we can't fix a date
for the cherry blossom camping trip.

62
00:06:07,908 --> 00:06:09,397
Don't feel bad.

63
00:06:09,398 --> 00:06:10,595
Everyone has a job.

64
00:06:10,596 --> 00:06:12,006
It's only right to be considerate.

65
00:06:12,007 --> 00:06:13,809
What's your plan for today?

66
00:06:14,310 --> 00:06:16,808
Me? I...

67
00:06:16,809 --> 00:06:18,709
I came a day early
to book a camping spot!

68
00:06:18,710 --> 00:06:21,621
While I'm at it,
I'm experiencing solo camping.

69
00:06:23,199 --> 00:06:25,397
Rin is camping alone too.

70
00:06:25,398 --> 00:06:27,606
I thought the timing was wonderful.

71
00:06:28,387 --> 00:06:30,012
This is my first time solo camping.

72
00:06:30,890 --> 00:06:33,711
Aki, you finally muster the courage
to try out solo camping.

73
00:06:34,211 --> 00:06:36,492
Stay safe on your way to the campsite.

74
00:06:37,798 --> 00:06:40,704
The whole trip is considering
camping until you reach the site.

75
00:06:40,705 --> 00:06:42,401
What is it called
when I reach the place?

76
00:06:43,193 --> 00:06:45,110
See you tomorrow.

77
00:06:45,111 --> 00:06:46,611
Sure. See you.

78
00:06:49,997 --> 00:06:52,006
The sunshine is so cosy.

79
00:06:52,007 --> 00:06:54,497
It's making me a bit sleepy.

80
00:06:59,301 --> 00:07:02,106
Almost all the cherry blossom trees
are in full bloom.

81
00:07:03,111 --> 00:07:05,960
I did my sketching
at the observatory square.

82
00:07:06,717 --> 00:07:08,809
I should try sketching
on the green square today.

83
00:07:15,508 --> 00:07:16,596
Someone is sleeping here.

84
00:07:17,195 --> 00:07:19,491
She is sleeping so soundly.

85
00:07:19,492 --> 00:07:22,008
Doesn't that hurt her back?

86
00:07:27,799 --> 00:07:31,606
There is a cute creature
hiding in the bag!

87
00:07:32,992 --> 00:07:34,392
A Pomeranian?

88
00:07:34,393 --> 00:07:36,392
No, probably a Chihuahua.

89
00:07:36,393 --> 00:07:38,204
Nope, that's not the point here.

90
00:07:38,205 --> 00:07:39,903
I have to finish the drawing today.

91
00:07:43,689 --> 00:07:44,606
All right.

92
00:07:45,799 --> 00:07:48,804
I wonder how much
I can draw by the evening.

93
00:08:03,393 --> 00:08:04,601
Just a little bit of sketching.

94
00:08:22,007 --> 00:08:23,584
I'm... I'm sorry!

95
00:08:23,585 --> 00:08:25,670
Well... You know...

96
00:08:25,671 --> 00:08:28,298
I just thought the dog looked cute
when it was asleep...

97
00:08:28,299 --> 00:08:29,611
-That's why...
-I see.

98
00:08:30,102 --> 00:08:31,798
You're really good at drawing.

99
00:08:31,799 --> 00:08:35,013
No... I'm terrible at drawing.

100
00:08:36,509 --> 00:08:39,293
Do you always link
this drawing pad to your smartphone?

101
00:08:39,294 --> 00:08:40,892
Do you mind if I give it a try?

102
00:08:40,893 --> 00:08:42,008
Be my guest.

103
00:08:44,303 --> 00:08:45,898
This thing is pretty neat.

104
00:08:48,804 --> 00:08:51,496
I've heard
how violent a Chihuahua could be.

105
00:08:51,497 --> 00:08:53,695
But this little guy here
is very tame.

106
00:08:54,584 --> 00:08:56,600
It's fallen asleep again.

107
00:08:56,601 --> 00:08:57,903
You're so cute.

108
00:08:58,704 --> 00:09:00,288
This thing isn't too bad at all.

109
00:09:00,289 --> 00:09:03,499
I want to get a tablet for my drawing,

110
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:05,506
but I just couldn't
spend that much money on one.

111
00:09:05,507 --> 00:09:08,299
Yeah. A tablet can be quite expensive.

112
00:09:11,393 --> 00:09:13,205
"ALARM"
Time to get working.

113
00:09:13,687 --> 00:09:15,105
Thanks for letting me use that.

114
00:09:15,106 --> 00:09:16,215
Don't mention it.

115
00:09:18,903 --> 00:09:21,195
See you around.
Good luck with your drawing.

116
00:09:25,903 --> 00:09:27,018
Ena, where are you now?

117
00:09:27,608 --> 00:09:29,109
I'm at the green square.

118
00:09:29,698 --> 00:09:30,794
All right.

119
00:09:34,496 --> 00:09:36,315
Hey there, Ena.

120
00:09:37,492 --> 00:09:38,601
I'm here.

121
00:09:39,705 --> 00:09:41,107
You actually came.

122
00:09:41,601 --> 00:09:43,606
I have some free time to kill anyway.

123
00:09:44,999 --> 00:09:47,002
You're still such a great artist.

124
00:09:47,591 --> 00:09:49,504
After you get into high school,

125
00:09:49,505 --> 00:09:52,110
you'll probably join the manga club
or the art club.

126
00:09:52,111 --> 00:09:55,407
I don't draw manga.

127
00:09:55,408 --> 00:09:57,804
And I don't think
I'll fit into the art club.

128
00:10:00,513 --> 00:10:03,293
I'd like to join a club
that studies illustration.

129
00:10:03,294 --> 00:10:06,299
I've never heard of a club like that.

130
00:10:06,897 --> 00:10:08,511
So, there isn't one.

131
00:10:08,512 --> 00:10:10,392
I guess I'll just go home after school.

132
00:10:10,393 --> 00:10:13,699
I'll work extra hard and save up money
to buy myself a drawing tablet.

133
00:10:13,700 --> 00:10:16,433
The one with the impressive stylus?

134
00:10:16,434 --> 00:10:18,105
Bingo.

135
00:10:18,106 --> 00:10:20,402
Why not ask your mum
to buy you one?

136
00:10:20,403 --> 00:10:22,704
Tell her it's a gift
for getting into high school.

137
00:10:23,298 --> 00:10:26,208
I don't think my parents
will ever buy me that kind of stuff.

138
00:10:32,398 --> 00:10:34,605
After getting into high school,

139
00:10:34,606 --> 00:10:36,605
I should find a hobby or something.

140
00:10:36,606 --> 00:10:39,012
There's no need to force yourself
into doing anything.

141
00:10:42,397 --> 00:10:45,501
But I want to be like you.

142
00:10:45,502 --> 00:10:47,502
I want to find my passion.

143
00:10:50,002 --> 00:10:51,705
I bought some snacks.
Would you like some?

144
00:10:52,395 --> 00:10:53,299
Sure.

