to show your peace sign.

173
00:13:02,102 --> 00:13:03,698
Let me have a look.

174
00:13:06,397 --> 00:13:09,386
That makes using the cardboard
stand-ins completely pointless!

175
00:13:09,393 --> 00:13:10,893
Onto the next spot, Nadeshiko.

176
00:13:14,393 --> 00:13:15,506
Sakura.

177
00:13:15,507 --> 00:13:18,507
Is there a bird pattern on that hill?

178
00:13:19,605 --> 00:13:21,617
It does look like a bird.

179
00:13:22,294 --> 00:13:24,100
What could it be?

180
00:13:24,101 --> 00:13:25,898
I wonder.

181
00:13:31,512 --> 00:13:33,491
KATSUNUMA

182
00:13:40,002 --> 00:13:41,496
Just today alone,

183
00:13:41,497 --> 00:13:43,622
I've already filled
the album with cherry blossoms.

184
00:13:44,599 --> 00:13:45,909
Everything is pink.

185
00:13:48,498 --> 00:13:52,195
There is a retro train in the park
in front of the station, Rin.

186
00:13:52,898 --> 00:13:55,013
Huh? Is this...

187
00:13:55,388 --> 00:13:57,409
JINROKU CHERRY BLOSSOMS PARK

188
00:14:01,605 --> 00:14:04,301
The train is so old-school and cute.

189
00:14:04,794 --> 00:14:05,612
Cute?

190
00:14:07,007 --> 00:14:08,200
An impression of the train.

191
00:14:10,700 --> 00:14:12,216
What is she doing?

192
00:14:13,701 --> 00:14:17,815
You're really into retro trains lately.

193
00:14:19,206 --> 00:14:21,402
After taking a ride
on the Abt System Railway in Oi River,

194
00:14:21,403 --> 00:14:23,908
I just fell in love with these trains.

195
00:14:24,805 --> 00:14:28,298
"TOKOGAWA RAILWAY MUSEUM"
I saw this on TV once.

196
00:14:28,299 --> 00:14:32,303
It says there is
a museum of retro trains in Gunma.

197
00:14:32,304 --> 00:14:33,398
Really?

198
00:14:33,799 --> 00:14:34,898
If I'm not mistaken...

199
00:14:35,801 --> 00:14:37,204
Found it. This is it.

200
00:14:37,205 --> 00:14:39,511
Yokogawa Railway Museum.

201
00:14:39,512 --> 00:14:40,897
Show me.

202
00:14:41,895 --> 00:14:44,351
"YOKOGAWA RAILWAY MUSEUM"
So many retro trains!

203
00:14:46,997 --> 00:14:50,305
They have an Abt System Train too.

204
00:14:51,211 --> 00:14:52,682
The location is...

205
00:14:54,204 --> 00:14:56,699
It's about the same distance
between here and Hamamatsu.

206
00:14:56,700 --> 00:14:58,205
It isn't that far from here.

207
00:14:58,995 --> 00:15:00,569
Maybe I should go solo camping in Gunma

208
00:15:00,570 --> 00:15:03,304
for my retro-train field study camp.

209
00:15:03,995 --> 00:15:06,601
It's better to go camping with everyone.

210
00:15:10,096 --> 00:15:11,403
Here you are.

211
00:15:14,606 --> 00:15:15,902
SOUTH IDE CAMPSITE

212
00:15:15,903 --> 00:15:19,002
The South Ide Campsite is only

213
00:15:19,610 --> 00:15:22,398
a 50-minute walk from the station.

214
00:15:23,601 --> 00:15:26,308
Plenty of cherry blossoms here too.

215
00:15:26,309 --> 00:15:28,803
I asked Rin about it beforehand,

216
00:15:28,804 --> 00:15:29,896
but there really is a toilet here.

217
00:15:29,897 --> 00:15:31,402
There's no water source.

218
00:15:31,403 --> 00:15:33,695
A rather challenging campsite indeed.

219
00:15:34,408 --> 00:15:38,502
But since there's no one here
and the site is free to use,

220
00:15:39,092 --> 00:15:40,599
this is likely a very secret camping spot.

221
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:42,402
Impressive, site hunter Rin Shima.
Great job.

222
00:15:43,415 --> 00:15:45,194
Setting the tent in no time.

223
00:15:46,403 --> 00:15:48,314
The bed for today is all set.

224
00:15:50,193 --> 00:15:51,512
Well then...

225
00:15:52,683 --> 00:15:53,792
When you go solo camping,

226
00:15:53,793 --> 00:15:57,497
it's important to plan a way
to kill your free time, Aki.

227
00:15:58,107 --> 00:16:01,297
Rin likes to read.
Nadeshiko experiments with her recipes.

228
00:16:01,298 --> 00:16:03,512
I can kill my time with...

229
00:16:06,413 --> 00:16:07,199
CINNAMON STICK

230
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:09,204
Homemade non-alcoholic cocktail!

231
00:16:10,395 --> 00:16:12,512
The non-alcoholic cocktail
we're making today is

232
00:16:12,513 --> 00:16:14,896
the Spicy Saratoga Cooler.

233
00:16:14,897 --> 00:16:17,308
It's a cocktail made with ginger ale.

234
00:16:17,996 --> 00:16:19,396
First, in a small pot,

235
00:16:19,397 --> 00:16:23,891
add 70cc of water
and 60 grams of coarse sugar and heat it.

236
00:16:23,892 --> 00:16:25,011
When the water boils,

237
00:16:25,012 --> 00:16:26,698
add one portion of lime peel,

238
00:16:26,699 --> 00:16:28,694
half a cinnamon stick,

239
00:16:28,695 --> 00:16:30,912
20 grams of fresh ginger slices,

240
00:16:30,913 --> 00:16:33,002
and a preferred amount of cloves.

241
00:16:33,700 --> 00:16:36,917
Since we are making spicy Saratoga Cooler,

242
00:16:36,918 --> 00:16:40,500
we'll use Havana chilli powder to replace
regular chili to bring out the spiciness.

243
00:16:40,501 --> 00:16:41,907
Gently...

244
00:16:42,501 --> 00:16:45,990
If you add too much Havana chilli powder,
it'll be extremely spicy.

245
00:16:45,991 --> 00:16:48,199
Be very careful.

246
00:16:48,798 --> 00:16:50,808
Cook for about three minutes
and then turn off the heat.

247
00:16:50,809 --> 00:16:52,490
After it has cooled slightly,

248
00:16:52,491 --> 00:16:55,803
add another 20 grams
of fresh ginger slices

249
00:16:55,804 --> 00:16:57,370
and let it ferment overnight.

250
00:16:57,371 --> 00:16:59,016
But I want to have it right away.

251
00:16:59,017 --> 00:17:00,912
So I'll just let it sit for an hour.

252
00:17:00,913 --> 00:17:02,495
Well then...

253
00:17:02,496 --> 00:17:05,397
While waiting for the syrup to cool,
I can pass my time with...

254
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:09,606
A homemade bracelet
made with paracord.

255
00:17:10,194 --> 00:17:12,913
I've always wanted to try this.

256
00:17:13,788 --> 00:17:15,198
"PARACORD"
The paracord

257
00:17:15,199 --> 00:17:19,402
is a high-strength parachute cord with
thin strands enclosed in a nylon sheath.

258
00:17:19,403 --> 00:17:23,085
The inner strands can be removed.

259
00:17:23,802 --> 00:17:29,214
The strands can be replaced with sewing
thread, dental floss, or fishing line.

260
00:17:29,215 --> 00:17:32,401
Some paracords even contain
combustible material inside,

261
00:17:32,402 --> 00:17:35,813
which can be used
to start a fire when necessary.

262
00:17:35,814 --> 00:17:39,908
It is a piece of outdoor equipment
that is more useful than it appears.

263
00:17:42,194 --> 00:17:44,402
Let's try making it right away.

264
00:17:45,897 --> 00:17:47,095
Like so.

265
00:17:47,096 --> 00:17:49,007
Then...

266
00:17:49,599 --> 00:17:51,513
Tie multiple knots.

267
00:17:52,006 --> 00:17:53,614
And the line goes through here.

268
00:17:54,398 --> 00:17:56,507
Burn the open ends.

269
00:17:57,295 --> 00:18:01,701
"COBRA KNOT PARACORD BRACELET"
The cobra knot paracord bracelet is ready.

270
00:18:02,706 --> 00:18:05,095
This is a lot easier than expected.

271
00:18:05,096 --> 00:18:07,200
Wearing it makes me feel
like a fashionable camper.

272
00:18:07,705 --> 00:18:09,101
Now...

273
00:18:09,102 --> 00:18:11,961
My ginger syrup should be ready by now.

274
00:18:12,397 --> 00:18:15,193
Put the pre-peeled lime into a glass,

275
00:18:15,194 --> 00:18:18,944
then pour in the ginger syrup
and sparkling water.

276
00:18:19,405 --> 00:18:22,601
The spicy Saratoga Cooler is now ready!

277
00:18:24,907 --> 00:18:28,397
This spicy aroma is quite appetizing.

278
00:18:31,390 --> 00:18:33,270
Too spicy! It's super spicy!

279
00:18:33,897 --> 00:18:36,501
It seems like I added
too much Havana chilli powder,

280
00:18:36,502 --> 00:18:39,199
but the taste is still quite good.

281
00:18:39,705 --> 00:18:42,897
I should dilute it a little
before drinking.

282
00:18:42,898 --> 00:18:45,502
By the way,
I still need to make some side dishes.

283
00:18:51,403 --> 00:18:53,007
All right. It's done.

284
00:18:54,699 --> 00:18:57,694
Sauted potatoes with sausages.

285
00:18:58,178 --> 00:18:59,002
A simple sauteed dish.

286
00:18:59,003 --> 00:19:00,794
But it should taste just right.

287
00:19:01,293 --> 00:19:03,099
Here goes nothing.

288
00:19:11,101 --> 00:19:12,606
This is awesome!

289
00:19:13,296 --> 00:19:16,908
The heat from an alcohol burner
is enough for a person's meal.

290
00:19:19,694 --> 00:19:21,809
Nice and relaxing.

291
00:19:23,103 --> 00:19:26,507
Now I understand why Rin
is so passionate about solo-camping.

292
00:19:28,505 --> 00:19:30,193
That's right. The teacher said,

293
00:19:30,194 --> 00:19:33,963
"I'll prepare the food for
our cherry blossom viewing trip tomorrow."

294
00:19:33,964 --> 00:19:35,006
What is she preparing?

295
00:19:35,799 --> 00:19:37,610
WINE

296
00:19:37,611 --> 00:19:39,022
This is concerning.

297
00:19:39,598 --> 00:19:41,798
I should finish the remaining potatoes.

298
00:19:41,799 --> 00:19:44,309
SPINACH CORN

299
00:19:49,897 --> 00:19:52,205
Another simple yet delicious dish.

300
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:57,814
Is this a stray from this area?

301
00:19:59,212 --> 00:20:01,199
Nope!

302
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:02,908
This is too much salt for a cat!

303
00:20:05,402 --> 00:20:07,309
Unbelievable.

304
00:20:07,887 --> 00:20:11,830
If I'm not mistaken,
a cat can have some apple.

305
00:20:12,204 --> 00:20:13,715
Wait there.

306
00:20:14,900 --> 00:20:15,804
Here you go.

307
00:20:19,700 --> 00:20:22,304
You look very clean for a stray.

308
00:20:23,163 --> 00:20:24,306
That's right.

309
00:20:27,007 --> 00:20:29,710
I found a cat at the campsite.

310
00:20:30,909 --> 00:20:33,506
You're having a great time over there.

311
00:20:33,507 --> 00:20:36,303
I wish you were here too, Inuko.

312
00:20:36,304 --> 00:20:38,600
I said I'd be busy today.

313
00:20:38,601 --> 00:20:39,987
We'll head there tomorrow.

314
00:20:39,988 --> 00:20:41,908
Enjoy your time alone tonight.

315
00:20:42,594 --> 00:20:43,908
Okay.

316
00:20:44,804 --> 00:20:47,804
Come on. Are you leaving already?

317
00:20:48,501 --> 00:20:50,815
Cats are so unpredictable.

318
00:20:50,816 --> 00:20:52,089
Whatever.

319
00:20:52,090 --> 00:20:54,111
I'm headed for the hot spring.

320
00:20:54,700 --> 00:20:57,006
WELCOME TO SOUTH IDE HOT SPRING

321
00:20:57,007 --> 00:20:59,601
Arrived at the hot spring.

322
00:21:02,512 --> 00:21:05,892
What? You live here?

323
00:21:10,596 --> 00:21:13,204
Long ago,

324
00:21:13,205 --> 00:21:15,506
there lived a girl named Chiaki Ohgaki.

325
00:21:15,507 --> 00:21:17,816
"SOUVENIR"
She was brought to a hot spring hotel

326
00:21:17,817 --> 00:21:19,788
by the cat she caught.

327
00:21:20,111 --> 00:21:24,517
But the hot spring is simply too comfy.

328
00:21:25,199 --> 00:21:29,908
She can feel it melting her.

329
00:21:33,908 --> 00:21:36,006
Not too hot, not too warm.

330
00:21:36,007 --> 00:21:36,903
Perfectly balanced.

331
00:21:40,398 --> 00:21:42,516
The cherry blossoms are still blooming
in the courtyard.

332
00:21:42,517 --> 00:21:44,496
Such a scenic view.

333
00:21:44,896 --> 00:21:46,996
Can't agree more.

334
00:21:51,298 --> 00:21:52,716
Huh? Inuko!

335
00:21:53,107 --> 00:21:54,896
What are you doing here?

336
00:23:27,895 --> 00:23:36,292
